## 👶 Toddler & Kids Survival Guide

### Packing Essentials for the 3-Year-Old

- [ ] Car seat / booster seat (for the long Innova drive)
- [ ] Diapers + wipes (enough for 4 days + road)
- [ ] Sunscreen SPF 50+ (baby-safe)
- [ ] Wide-brim sun hat
- [ ] Swim diapers for beach
- [ ] Portable snack containers (biscuits, fruit, dry snacks)
- [ ] Water bottles (refillable) for all kids
- [ ] Light stroller (optional — beaches are sandy though)
- [ ] First-aid kit: ORS, Crocin drops, band-aids, mosquito repellent patches
- [ ] Inflatable arm floats / puddle jumper vest
- [ ] Change of clothes in car (for spills/accidents)

### Beach Safety Rules for Kids

1. **Always** swim where there are lifeguards 🚩
2. **Benaulim & Palolem** have the calmest waves — best for toddler
3. Keep toddler in **ankle-deep water only**
4. Avoid beaches during **12 PM–3 PM** (peak heat in April)
5. Apply sunscreen **every 2 hours**
6. Watch for **jellyfish** — ask locals before entering water
7. Carry **ORS packets** — kids dehydrate fast in Goa heat

### Kid-Friendly Food Orders

For the picky eaters in the family:
- **Butter garlic prawns** (mild, universally loved)
- **Rava-fried fish** (crispy, no spice)
- **French fries** (available everywhere)
- **Grilled chicken** (if seafood-ed out)
- **Pasta/pizza** (most beach shacks have them)
- **Fresh lime soda** (sweet version)
- **Mango lassi / milkshakes**

### Toddler Nap Schedule Integration

| Time | Plan Around It |
|---|---|
| **1:30–3:30 PM** | Schedule drives during this window — toddler sleeps in car |
| **7:30–8:00 PM** | Aim to start dinner by 7 PM so toddler doesn't melt down |
| **Morning** | Leave for activities by 9 AM before it gets too hot |

